Hi guys!

  I have a problem with JUnit framework. Each time i try to launch a class as a 
JUnit task I've got exception:

java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: junit.framework.TestCase.getName()
Ljava/lang/String;
	at org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.runner.RemoteTestRunner.getTestName
(RemoteTestRunner.java:616)
	at org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.runner.RemoteTestRunner.sendTree
(RemoteTestRunner.java:589)
	at org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.runner.RemoteTestRunner.sendTree
(RemoteTestRunner.java:585)
	at org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.runner.RemoteTestRunner.runTests
(RemoteTestRunner.java:414)
	at org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.runner.RemoteTestRunner.run
(RemoteTestRunner.java:305)
	at org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.runner.RemoteTestRunner.main
(RemoteTestRunner.java:186)

  Class example is below:

package com.classic.xyz;

import org.apache.log4j.Logger;

import junit.framework.*;

public class MainTest extends TestCase {
	private static Logger log = Logger.getLogger(MainTest.class);

	public MainTest(String testName) {
		super(testName);
	}

	public static TestSuite suite(){
		TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();
		suite.addTest(new MainTest("testCalculator"));
		return suite;
	}

	public void testCalculator()
	throws Exception {
		String logStr = "testCalculator() : ";
		log.debug(logStr + "start");

		log.debug(logStr + "end");
	}

}

Cheers, Andrei
